parameters:
Tavern Master: "This town doesn't pay exorbitant taxes to the royal
capital. Even the officials can't stand up to the resistance in this
town."
Luuna: What are you doing in a place like this?

Sylvia: Hilda is saying she's getting hungry for human flesh. We're
looking for a tasty-looking child.
Sylvia: So, what will you do?

Sylvia: Luuna, I know you well. After all, you were once a student of
mine.

Sylvia: As you are now, you can't reach the level of me, Lucia, or
even Hilda. That's what you think, isn't it, Luuna?
Sylvia: That's why you all came to Norva-Na.
Sylvia: I'm asking how much you've leveled up.

Luuna: Sylvia, the resistance fighters of Norva-Na are all elites.
It's not just me alone.
Sylvia: I don't know what tricks you have up your sleeve.
Sylvia: But I have no intention of fighting here. Goodbye.
Luuna: (Sylvia is right... I'm nowhere near her level yet.)

Cain: Are those girls really that dangerous? To me, they just look
like a couple of sisters.
Becky: Sigh... Just be quiet, will you?
Luuna: Sorry, both of you. I'm fine.

Man: "Valentina is a prestigious magic school, the best in the world.
It's also a place where magicians below average receive their
baptism."

Man: "Receiving the queen's baptism is said to increase one's magical
power, but I've heard that Sylvia is the one who decides whether or
not you'll be accepted for the baptism."
